  <li id="comment-42065" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">annabel</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=51#comment-42065"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2014-12-14T07:53:33-05:00">Sunday, December 14, 2014 at 7:53 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I made a half recipe of the 3-layer peppermint bark today (that&#39;s how much ghiradelli I had in the cupboard), and here are two tips for anyone else making it. Next time I will melt the white chocolate in two batches; I should have used more in the first layer, and if I just melted 2/3rds first that would solve that problem. Also, I think I will just line a suitable size plastic container with foil, I was not so good at spreading it out evenly on the cooky sheet. And, Trader Joe&#39;s white chocolate chips have cocoa butter as the second ingredient after sugar and are only $1.99 for ten ounces.</p>
    </div>

